  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering at both national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National Legislation:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act (various countries)\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Transaction Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Compliance Measures:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious activities\n- Record-keeping requirements\n- Enhanced scrutiny for high-risk transactions\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms:\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Substantial financial penalties\n- Asset seizure\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n\n5. Key Sectors Regulated:\n- Banking\n- Financial institutions\n- Cryptocurrency exchanges\n- Real estate\n- Legal and accounting professions\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute money laundering activities through comprehensive regulatory approaches.",
